@Joseph M. Popular Linux Distributions like Ubuntu or Linux Mint have no shortcomings even when used for general purpose computing. For specific applications like embedded systems and severs Linux is the most commonly used Kernel because it's open source and customisable like no other Closed Sourced Kernel.
